query.result:
**English:**

112 He who appears so robust and who agrees,
113 singing, with him of the masculine nose,
114 wore the cord of every worthiness;

115 and if after him the young man who sits behind him
116 had remained king,
117 the worthiness would have passed from vessel to vessel,

118 which cannot be said of the other lines;
119 James and Frederick have the kingdoms;
120 no one possesses the better inheritance.

